'''''Star Wars'' 33''' is the thirty-third issue of the [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (2015)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Jason Aaron]] and illustrated by [[Salvador Larroca]]. It was released on [[July 5]], [[2017]].

==Publisher's summary==
''*''The Hero of the Rebellion & the Princess of the Revolution!''''
''*''Luke'' and Leia finally get some time alone&hellip;''''
''*''Unfortunately, it's stranded on a desert island''.''

==Opening crawl==
{{OpeningCrawl
|name=REBELS IN THE WILD
|text=It is a time of turmoil in the galaxy. While the evil
Galactic Empire remains strong, the Rebel Alliance
continues to fight for freedom.

Luke Skywalker struggles with his destiny. He can feel the
Force, but lacks the training to become a Jedi Knight.
When Doctor Aphra approaches him with an artifact
containing the consciousness of an ancient Jedi, Luke
accompanies her to the Citadel of Ktath'atn. Overcome with
telepathic parasites, Luke is able to overcome their
control and free the people of the Citadel along with
Rebellion leader Princess Leia.

Despite this, danger still lurks as the surviving
parasites aren't the only ones hunting for Luke and
Leia....
}}

==Plot summary==
After their ship is damaged by a nebula they entered to escape Imperial forces, Luke Skywalker and Leia Organa are forced to crash-land on an unknown planet. The planet is almost entirely covered by water, leaving them stranded on a small, isolated island. For three weeks, they survive on their own, hunting for food and repairing what they can of their ship. During this time, they share stories and connect over their similar pasts as orphans, strengthening their bond.

Luke and Leia soon discover they are not alone on the planet when a group of humanoid creatures emerge from the ocean. They realize that a whole civilization has been living beneath the waves the entire time. However, their short-lived peace is interrupted when the Empire tracks them down. An AT-AT walker'and a team of Imperial stormtroopers emerge from the water to capture them.

Using her wits and wilderness survival skills, Leia prepares a series of booby traps. The stormtroopers trigger a trap that fires paralyzing quills at them, giving Luke the chance to take out the remaining troopers with his lightsaber. To deal with the menacing AT-AT, Leia shoots a flaming arrow at a pile of dry wood she had strategically placed earlier. The ensuing explosion engulfs the walker, destroying it completely. With the threat eliminated, Luke and Leia scavenge enough parts from the wreckage of the AT-AT to repair their own ship. They are able to fly away from the planet, leaving the newly discovered civilization undisturbed.

